    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-22T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-22T04:00:00-05:00" n="770"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/2230</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-22T09:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1918, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.01 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5953. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 621. The following is the text of official communication received to-day from
                    General <persName>Dawes</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Colonel <persName>Corbusier</persName> has been directed this date to
                            immediately cancel all contracts for animals both in Spain and Portugal,
                            and that all purchases of animals would be stopped as soon as possible
                            in accordance with terms of contracts. Total number of animals received
                            from Spain to date as reported is 11,590. It is estimated that no more
                            than 4,000 animals will be received after contracts are canceled.
                            Signed, Rogers, Quartermaster General, Army.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>In connection with foregoing we are informed by Senator
                        <persName>Hollis</persName> that no definite promise as regards compensation
                    was given by him to the Spanish Government other than his personal assurance of
                    a recommendation to the War Trade Board to release 20,000 tons of sulphate of
                    ammonia on a basis of securing the release from Spain of 50,000 animals for
                    shipment to France. It is therefore our understanding that it is optional with
                    you as to whether or not you wish to release the sulphate of ammonia to Spain.
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
